  "text": "Plasmids and siRNAs. pGL2-E24BS contains 4 high-affinity E2 binding sites upstream of a simian virus 40 (SV40) promoter which drives luciferase expression [CITATION_1] . Expression plasmids used include pCG-E2, pCMV␤-p300, pRSV-CBP, and pCI-pCAF. All E2 mutations from lysine to arginine (R) were generated with the Quikchange II site-directed mutagenesis system according to the manufacturer's specifications (Agilent Technologies) using pCG-E2 as a template. The ⌬NcoI BPV-1 genome does not express E2 due to a deletion within the E2 reading frame [CITATION_2] . p300 (CAGAGCAGUCCUGGAUUAG), CBP (AAUCCACAGUACCGA GAAAUG), and pCAF (UCGCCGUGAAGAAAGCGCA) custom siRNAs and control predesigned siRNA (AM4635) were purchased from Ambion.",
